==English==
===Verb===
# '''a.''' ''obsolete''. to bloom, burst forth into flowers. '''b.''' to burst forth into something resembling a flower. '''c.''' to burst forth as a plant when flowering; [[construe|construed]] with ''into''
# ''chemistry.'' '''a.''' of a crystalline substance: To change over the surface, or throughout, to "flowers" or fine powder, owing to the loss of the water of crystallization on exposure to the air. '''b.''' of a salt: to come (in solution) to the surface (of the ground, etc.) and there crystallize. ''also,'' to form a crust (by [[capillary]] attraction and evaporation) on the sides of a vessel containing a solution. '''c.''' of the ground, a wall, etc.: to become covered with a powdery crust of saline particles left by evaporation from a solution which has been drawn to the surface by capillary attraction
# ''fig.'' '''a.''' to ‘blossom out’, break out into brilliant display. '''b.''' of hidden [[agencies]], etc.: to come to the surface, become [[manifest]]